{{About|a European internet sale|the American shopping event|Black Friday (shopping)}} '''Black Friday Sale''' is a joint sales initiative by hundreds of online vendors in [[Germany]], [[Austria]] and [[Switzerland]], inspired by the American [[Black Friday (shopping)|Black Friday]]. The event was first launched on 28 November 2013: Over its 24-hour run, more than 1.2 million people visited the site, making it the single largest online shopping event in German speaking countries. Many leading online retailers such as [[Zalando]], [[Disney Store]], [[Saturn (store)|Saturn]], [[Galeria Kaufhof]], [[Heinrich Deichmann-Schuhe GmbH|Deichmann]], [[The Body Shop]], [[Sony]], [[Yves Rocher]] and [[Dell]] participated in the event in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.welt.de/icon/article121825365/Der-absolute-Festtag-des-Online-Shoppers.html|title=German online newspaper Welt | date=22 November 2013}}</ref>
== Reception == Once the Black Friday Sale started at 7 pm on 28 November 2013, more than 50.000 users simultaneously accessed the site, temporarily causing delays and server overloads. The overwhelming numbers of visitors also caused the servers of several online shops, such as the electronics store Saturn, to suffer significant downtime.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.channelobserver.de/artikel/black-friday-server-von-saturn-geht-in-die-knie-1522/|title=German online magazine Channel Observer | date=2 December 2013}}</ref> Despite the technical problems, the first Black Friday Sale generated a significant turnover and was considered a notable success by online retailers and organizers alike.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.internetworld.de/e-commerce/internet/black-friday-sale-erfolg-294371.html|title=German magazine Internet World Business | date=4 December 2013}}</ref>
== Upcoming events == After successfully launching in 2013, and having a successful 2014, 2015 and 2016, the Black Friday Sale is set to return on 24 November 2017. Online shoppers are expected to spend billions on this Black Friday sale.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Black Friday Sale 2017|url=http://thelifetech.com/hostgator-black-friday-sale/|website=TheLifeTech|accessdate=21 November 2017}}</ref> Once more, several hundred leading online vendors will be involved, among them [[Douglas Holding]], [[Hewlett-Packard|HP]], [[Sony]], [[Tally Weijl]] and [[Weltbild]]. [[eBay]] and [[PayPal]] are also featured as official partners of the event.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.moebelkultur.de/news/black_friday_sale-onlinehndler_erwarten_auch_in_diesem_jahr_rekordumstze/21126.html|title=German magazine Moebelkultur | date=24 September 2014}}</ref>
