{{Infobox company | name = Jetta International | logo = Jetta-logo.png | type = [[Private company|Private]] | genre = | foundation = 1991 | founder = | location_city = [[Monmouth Junction, New Jersey]] | location_country = [[United States]] | location = <!-- this parameter modifies "Headquarters" --> | key_people = | area_served = East Coast of the United States | industry = Electronics | products = [[Laptop|Notebook]]s | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | owner = | homepage = [http://www.jettaus.com/ www.jettaus.com, Now Defunct] | dissolved = | footnotes = }} '''Jetta International''' is an [[United States of America|American]] [[original equipment manufacturer]] (OEM) and designer of computer [[laptop]]s, mainly operating in the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]]. The company was established in 1991,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jettaus.com/Article/About|title=About Jetta|publisher=Jetta International}}</ref> and is based in [[Monmouth Junction, New Jersey]], (close to [[Princeton, New Jersey|Princeton]]), where its only manufacturing plant is located.
''Jetbook'', the laptop series manufactured by Jetta, has [[Intel]] [[microprocessor]]s and is supplied with a customizable selection of software. Jetbooks are known in the open source community because they can be purchased without a pre-installed [[operating system]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tuxmobil.org/jetta.html|title=Linux Laptop & Notebook Installation Guides: Jetta|publisher=TuxMobil}}</ref>
