The '''Ministry of Energy of the Russian Federation''' is, since 2008, the [[Russia]]n federal ministry responsible for energy policy.

This ministry was created in May 2008 as part of a reorganization by the incoming government of [[President of Russia|President]] [[Dmitry Medvedev]]. It is headquartered in [[Moscow]]. The former Ministry of Industry and Energy was turned into the [[Ministry of Industry (Russia)|Ministry of Industry]], whose present Minister is [[Viktor Khristenko]], gaining responsibility for trade policy from the former Ministry of Economic Development and Trade, but losing responsibility for energy policy, which was split off into the new Ministry of Energy. The former Federal Agency for Energy ([[Rosenergo]]) was also merged into the new Ministry of Energy.<ref>{{cite news | title = Restructuring without Repopulating | work = [[Kommersant]] | date = 13 May 2008 | url = http://commersant.com/p891024/r_1/Prime_Minister_Vladimir_Putin_government/}}</ref>

