{{Infobox company | name = SeeReal Technologies GmbH | logo = [[Image:SeeReal Technologies GmbH logo.png|200px|SeeReal Technologies GmbH logo]] | type = LLC (GmbH) | foundation = 2002 | location_city = Dresden | location_country = Germany | num_employees = > 30 | industry = Electronics, [[Volumetric display|Volumetric display technologies]] | products = [[Holography|Holographic]] and [[Autostereoscopy|Autostereoscopic]] Displays | homepage = {{URL|www.seereal.com}} |}}
'''SeeReal Technologies''' GmbH is a [[Dresden]]-based company focusing on the development of [[3D display]] solutions. It is owned by its [[Luxembourg]] parent company SeeReal Technologies S.A., which is responsible for marketing, partnering and IP licensing.
The firm was founded in 2002 by Dr. Armin Schwerdtner, who had previously headed an optics research group at the [[Dresden University of Technology]] (TU Dresden).
SeeReal develops technology that is licensed to display manufacturers, including several variants of a tracked autostereoscopic display.
The firm has presented a real-time desktop holographic display on the [[Society for Information Display|SID]] 2007 Display Week in [[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]] ([[California]]) and the [https://web.archive.org/web/20071019052128/http://techon.nikkeibp.co.jp/fpd/2007/english/ FPD] 2007 in [[Yokohama]] ([[Japan]]).<ref>{{Cite_journal|title = SeeReal develops practical real-time holographic display|author = Gail Overton|journal = Laser Focus World|publisher = PennWell Corporation|date = September 2007|volume = 43|issue = 9|url = https://www.laserfocusworld.com/articles/print/volume-43/issue-9/world-news/holography-seereal-develops-practical-real-time-holographic-display.html}} </ref> The firm owns more than 100 patents in the field of [[holography|holographic]] and [[autostereoscopy|autostereoscopic]] 3D displays {{Citation needed|date=April 2009}}.
SeeReal has won several awards, including the [[European IST Grand Prize|“European Information Society Technologies Prize (IST)”]] and the [https://web.archive.org/web/20070108232810/http://www.einfallsreich-sachsen.de/index.php?content=inno&sub=wettbewerb&sub3=infos “Innovation Prize of the Free State of Saxony”].
